WEBVTT

00:21.271 --> 00:23.523
Oh, I believe we've arrived.

00:23.606 --> 00:25.358
Oh, Paris.

00:25.442 --> 00:27.152
Oh.

00:29.654 --> 00:31.197
Oh, and it feels just the same.

00:31.281 --> 00:32.531
It's been waiting for us.

00:33.992 --> 00:36.870
I told Jean
I prefer never to look back,

00:36.953 --> 00:38.204
but that's not entirely true,

00:38.288 --> 00:40.165
not when the past
looks like this.

00:40.248 --> 00:43.752
I was an embryo here,
just getting started.

00:43.835 --> 00:46.254
But you have a legacy, Paul.

00:46.338 --> 00:48.506
You left a mark.

00:48.590 --> 00:49.674
Two days.

00:49.758 --> 00:50.759
Just the two of us.

01:06.608 --> 01:08.026
- Hmm?
- Go on and check us in.

01:08.109 --> 01:10.987
I'll, uh--
I'll handle this scoundrel.

01:11.071 --> 01:13.073
- Don't hurt him too much.
- No, no, no, no, no, no.

01:23.917 --> 01:26.252
- Bonjour.
- Oh, bonjour.

01:26.336 --> 01:28.129
Julia.

01:28.213 --> 01:30.423
- Julia!
- Avis!

01:30.507 --> 01:31.549
Oh.
They told me

01:31.633 --> 01:33.218
your train from Nice
had a slight delay.

01:33.301 --> 01:34.678
But you're right on schedule.

01:34.761 --> 01:36.596
Yes, we made up time.

01:37.764 --> 01:38.932
What are you doing here?

01:39.015 --> 01:40.350
- You invited me.
- I did?

01:40.433 --> 01:41.559
Yes.

01:41.643 --> 01:43.269
You wrote, "You must
come to France."

01:43.353 --> 01:44.270
So I did.

01:44.354 --> 01:46.606
Well, that's just
a thing people say.

01:46.690 --> 01:48.066
I've made friends
with the front desk clerk.

01:48.149 --> 01:49.275
He's a lovely guy.

01:49.359 --> 01:51.777
Long story short,
we have adjoining rooms.

01:52.862 --> 01:54.030
Oh.

01:59.411 --> 02:00.620
You all right, Paul?

02:00.704 --> 02:02.080
Oh, I'm great.

02:02.163 --> 02:03.498
I've really missed this.

02:03.581 --> 02:05.834
Can you believe it?

02:05.917 --> 02:07.168
Paris.

02:07.252 --> 02:09.003
I'm going to be a flaneur again
for two straight days.

02:09.086 --> 02:09.963
You?

02:10.045 --> 02:12.340
No flaneusing for me, alas.

02:12.424 --> 02:13.633
I wish.

02:13.717 --> 02:16.469
I have an Alp's worth
of work in my briefcase.

02:16.553 --> 02:18.430
I'm allowing myself
one lunch

02:18.513 --> 02:20.015
with an old pal I used to edit.

02:20.098 --> 02:21.016
Anyone I know?

02:22.100 --> 02:23.393
- Ooh.
- Hmm.

02:31.026 --> 02:34.612
I'm just getting
some fresh air, mon chÃ©ri.

02:34.696 --> 02:36.698
Save some for me.

02:36.781 --> 02:38.199
Oh, I thought
you'd never come.

02:39.284 --> 02:41.828
- Champagne?
- Oh, darling.

02:41.911 --> 02:43.704
You shouldn't have.

02:43.788 --> 02:45.165
To gay Paris.

02:45.248 --> 02:48.001
To gay Paris.

02:48.084 --> 02:49.127
Mm.

02:49.210 --> 02:51.588
Let's really go to town,
as they say.

02:51.671 --> 02:52.714
Indulge.

02:52.797 --> 02:53.840
Forget our troubles.

02:53.923 --> 02:55.716
Come on, get happy.

02:55.800 --> 02:56.885
The thing is, Avis--

02:56.968 --> 02:59.179
- Julie!
- Paul--

02:59.262 --> 03:01.389
be back in a flash.

03:09.397 --> 03:10.774
Oh.

03:15.028 --> 03:16.529
Where should we go first?

03:16.613 --> 03:18.615
Jeu de Paume?
L'Orangerie?

03:18.698 --> 03:20.200
No museums.

03:20.283 --> 03:21.409
No museums?

03:21.493 --> 03:22.911
No.
I think I'd rather be

03:22.994 --> 03:25.954
a tourist of our past
this time.

03:26.039 --> 03:27.123
Poet.

03:27.207 --> 03:28.458
So much has changed.

03:28.541 --> 03:30.669
Even in these last few months
with Simca,

03:30.752 --> 03:33.713
I sometimes feel like
I'm losing track of who I am.

03:33.797 --> 03:35.131
Hmm.

03:35.215 --> 03:39.219
Maybe if we went back
to where it all started--

03:39.302 --> 03:41.388
to Le Cordon Bleu.

03:42.514 --> 03:44.307
I see it.

03:44.391 --> 03:47.352
I may even have
some surprises up my sleeve.

03:47.435 --> 03:50.021
- And down my pants.
- Ha!

03:50.105 --> 03:53.316
I'll call to tell them.
Then we can be on our way.

03:53.400 --> 03:56.027
You hold that thought,
Paulski.

03:56.111 --> 03:58.863
You've made me all
hot and bothered.

03:58.947 --> 04:01.449
I may just need
to air out the merchandise.

04:04.911 --> 04:06.830
You were saying?

04:06.913 --> 04:08.498
Cigarette?

04:08.581 --> 04:10.959
Oh, I shouldn't.

04:11.042 --> 04:14.004
Well, just a puff
for old times' sake.

04:17.339 --> 04:19.426
- Were you smoking?
- No.

04:19.509 --> 04:21.302
You know I don't smoke alone.

04:21.386 --> 04:23.138
Or--or drink alone.

04:23.221 --> 04:24.681
Yet.

04:24.764 --> 04:28.351
No, it's
just the aroma of Paris.

04:28.435 --> 04:29.728
I'm running away.

04:29.811 --> 04:32.022
How fabulous.

04:32.105 --> 04:33.857
From what?

04:33.940 --> 04:36.317
I know we're running away,
but so what?

04:36.401 --> 04:39.237
Let's embrace
our final weekend in the past,

04:39.320 --> 04:41.322
before we are thrust
back into the hustle

04:41.406 --> 04:42.824
and bustle of the present.

04:42.907 --> 04:45.368
None of that
until the plane lands.

04:45.452 --> 04:46.911
- Okay, kitten?
- Hmm?

04:48.329 --> 04:50.040
It's a little warm
for hot chocolate.

04:50.123 --> 04:53.293
But oh, shit, it's legendary.

04:53.376 --> 04:56.421
And it's not like I'm coming
back when the weather turns.

04:56.504 --> 05:00.842
The thing is, Avis,
dear, Paul has--oh.

05:00.925 --> 05:03.470
Don't be alarmed, Julia,
but there's a tiny woman

05:03.553 --> 05:04.596
on the next balcony

05:04.679 --> 05:05.847
who bears
a striking resemblance

05:05.930 --> 05:08.183
to a lush we sometimes
entertain in Cambridge.

05:08.266 --> 05:09.476
You don't say.

05:09.559 --> 05:11.519
Well, the jig is up.

05:11.603 --> 05:13.646
The thing is, Avis, dear,

05:13.730 --> 05:16.900
Paul is planning a
rather remarkable romantic trip

05:16.983 --> 05:19.277
down Memory Lane
for us this weekend.

05:21.613 --> 05:23.365
Well, why
didn't you just say so?

05:23.448 --> 05:25.408
Well, because you came
all this way

05:25.492 --> 05:28.119
based on my rhetorical
invitation.

05:28.203 --> 05:29.704
I am perfectly capable

05:29.788 --> 05:32.415
of entertaining myself
in Paris.

05:32.499 --> 05:33.667
And you don't mind?

05:33.750 --> 05:36.044
Mind?
I insist.

05:36.127 --> 05:38.463
Just not too romantic.

05:39.714 --> 05:41.383
We share a wall.

05:50.225 --> 05:51.558
Sorry I'm late.

05:51.643 --> 05:52.811
Oh, no need.
No need.

05:52.894 --> 05:55.313
You're here for the big news.

05:55.397 --> 05:57.732
Now, gentlemen, as we all know,

05:57.816 --> 06:00.026
things can't continue
the way they've been going.

06:00.110 --> 06:01.569
As much as I hem and haw

06:01.653 --> 06:03.571
about fresh ideas
and new content,

06:03.655 --> 06:06.991
I need to put my money
where my mouth is.

06:07.075 --> 06:09.119
I've made
the difficult decision

06:09.202 --> 06:12.455
to cancel "I've Been Reading."

06:12.539 --> 06:13.915
This is their doing.

06:13.998 --> 06:16.209
Hunter, I know
his audience is limited,

06:16.292 --> 06:17.961
but as a non-reader,

06:18.044 --> 06:20.463
I have learned
so much from "Reading."

06:20.547 --> 06:23.091
The show, not actually reading.

06:24.676 --> 06:27.053
Don't succumb
to a female agenda.

06:27.137 --> 06:29.931
I appreciate that, uh, Roman,

06:30.015 --> 06:32.683
but this has nothing to do
with those ladies.

06:32.767 --> 06:34.310
I'd save it if I could.

06:34.394 --> 06:35.937
I've racked my head
against the wall

06:36.021 --> 06:38.023
trying to figure out how.

06:38.106 --> 06:39.441
If I may?

06:39.524 --> 06:41.776
I--I just think you need
to try some noisier guests.

06:41.860 --> 06:42.986
Controversial.

06:43.069 --> 06:44.070
Provocative.

06:44.154 --> 06:45.196
Dangerous, even.

06:45.280 --> 06:46.781
Like who?

06:46.865 --> 06:49.075
Off the top of my head,
I don't know--

06:49.159 --> 06:51.828
Helen Gurley Brown,
"Sex and the Single Girl."

06:51.911 --> 06:53.705
See if he can step up
to the times.

06:53.788 --> 06:56.582
Albert and
"Sex and the Single Girl"?

06:56.666 --> 07:00.420
I, for one, have never
been a sexual single girl.

07:00.503 --> 07:02.672
I've barely been
a sexual married man.

07:02.756 --> 07:05.383
I can't speak to the content.

07:05.467 --> 07:07.093
Alice?

07:07.177 --> 07:08.094
Hmm?
What?

07:08.178 --> 07:10.805
You're single, right?

07:10.889 --> 07:13.350
What--what do you mean?

07:13.433 --> 07:15.560
Is sex interesting to you?

07:21.232 --> 07:22.442
I gotta pee.

07:24.569 --> 07:25.904
Lovely.

07:25.987 --> 07:29.032
Um, doesn't exactly
instill confidence.

07:31.910 --> 07:32.952
Oh! Jeez.

07:33.036 --> 07:34.287
- Oh.
- Oh, sorry.

07:34.371 --> 07:35.372
That's all right.
It's all right.

07:35.455 --> 07:37.123
Sorry.
Oh, hey, Russ.

07:37.207 --> 07:40.210
Um, seeing as Hunter
sort of wants new ideas from us

07:40.293 --> 07:41.711
yesterday, I was wondering

07:41.795 --> 07:42.712
if you could spare
a few minutes

07:42.796 --> 07:43.880
to spitball with me.

07:43.963 --> 07:46.216
Spitball?
I love the TV lingo, pal.

07:46.299 --> 07:47.884
Did Elaine teach you that?

07:47.967 --> 07:48.885
But no can do.

07:48.968 --> 07:51.012
I've got an anti-war movement
to spotlight.

07:51.096 --> 07:52.305
I'm actually meeting
some members

07:52.389 --> 07:53.932
of the Socialist Party
of America.

07:54.015 --> 07:55.725
Socialism.
Radical.

07:55.808 --> 07:57.018
Day one of pilot filming.

07:57.102 --> 07:59.187
The great work begins.

07:59.270 --> 08:01.189
Well, good luck.

08:01.272 --> 08:02.440
Are you okay?

08:02.524 --> 08:05.276
Me?
Why do you--why do you ask?

08:05.360 --> 08:08.196
You're looking
a little sweaty.

08:08.279 --> 08:09.280
Are you feeling all right?

08:09.364 --> 08:10.490
- Oh.
- Oh.

08:10.573 --> 08:12.617
No, no, no.
Let me try that again.

08:12.701 --> 08:14.869
Marian tells me women
don't appreciate

08:14.953 --> 08:17.038
those kinds of observations.

08:17.122 --> 08:18.415
She definitely doesn't.

08:18.498 --> 08:20.875
Ixnay on the weatsay.

08:20.959 --> 08:23.003
More like a glow.

08:23.086 --> 08:24.713
A misty glow.

08:24.796 --> 08:26.423
You're glowing, Alice.

08:35.140 --> 08:36.390
Julia?

08:45.400 --> 08:47.777
Oh, Monsieur Bugnard.

08:47.861 --> 08:50.071
Monsieur Bugnard.

10:36.469 --> 10:37.554
But it's true.

10:37.637 --> 10:39.597
It's all meaningless.

10:39.681 --> 10:41.182
You can't stop, Jean-Paul.

10:41.266 --> 10:42.392
You can't stop writing.

10:42.475 --> 10:45.145
Why?
What's the point?

10:45.228 --> 10:47.814
I understand that
just like any writer,

10:47.897 --> 10:50.316
I'm doomed to tell
the same story

10:50.400 --> 10:51.526
until the day I die.

10:51.609 --> 10:53.486
But having that knowledge?

10:53.570 --> 10:58.700
It just makes it, uh,
not only futile, but petty.

10:58.783 --> 10:59.743
Okay.

10:59.826 --> 11:00.827
You're bringing me down, JP.

11:00.910 --> 11:02.287
I have one day in Paris.

11:02.370 --> 11:07.167
I wanna be inspired,
rekindled, awed.

11:07.250 --> 11:08.376
Try Camus.

11:08.460 --> 11:09.419
Maybe he's in town.

11:09.502 --> 11:10.795
How can you be so flip?

11:10.879 --> 11:12.589
This is your life's work.

11:12.672 --> 11:16.217
And for whatever it's worth,
this is my life's work, too.

11:16.301 --> 11:18.595
And you telling me
my life is meaningless

11:18.678 --> 11:21.222
is, frankly, pissing me off.

11:21.306 --> 11:23.016
Well, I'm sorry
it's pissing you off,

11:23.099 --> 11:25.060
but that does not make it
less true.

11:25.143 --> 11:26.269
Open your eyes.

11:26.353 --> 11:28.646
All that survives is crap.

11:28.730 --> 11:30.190
The Bible--garbage.

11:30.273 --> 11:32.567
It does not even hold up
dramaturgically.

11:32.650 --> 11:36.237
Shakespeare--incomprehensible,
sentimental tripe.

11:36.321 --> 11:37.238
Enough.

11:37.322 --> 11:39.491
Another word on the subject,
and I'm leaving.

11:39.574 --> 11:41.534
I didn't come all the way here
to get a lecture.

11:43.828 --> 11:48.625
Maybe Bugs Bunny--
he has insight.

11:48.708 --> 11:52.128
Apart from that,
I'm drawing a blank.

11:52.212 --> 11:53.755
A Mel Blanc.

11:55.674 --> 11:58.510
This place has a really nice
junior high school vibe.

11:58.593 --> 12:01.930
I hadn't thought of myself
as having cooties in 20 years.

12:02.013 --> 12:03.973
Julia talks about
a confederacy of women,

12:04.057 --> 12:05.725
although I'm pretty sure
she meant a sisterhood

12:05.809 --> 12:07.268
and not a traitorous army.

12:07.352 --> 12:09.270
Well, whatever she meant,
we really need her back.

12:09.354 --> 12:11.523
I mean, we need reinforcements.

12:11.606 --> 12:12.899
I have an idea for a show.

12:12.982 --> 12:14.484
For our female audience--

12:14.567 --> 12:16.986
Julia's audience--
as per Hunter's instructions.

12:17.070 --> 12:21.074
This is why I said yes when
you asked me to take this job.

12:21.157 --> 12:22.951
Okay.

12:27.330 --> 12:28.915
Maybe we should take
our brainstorming session

12:28.998 --> 12:30.041
someplace else.

12:30.125 --> 12:31.126
Dinner tomorrow night?

12:31.209 --> 12:32.752
Yes. You're on.

12:32.836 --> 12:36.256
I know a mediocre diner
I can afford on my GBH salary.

12:36.339 --> 12:37.590
Breakfast all day.

12:37.674 --> 12:38.758
Oh. How are the eggs?

12:38.842 --> 12:40.635
Greasy and great.

12:40.719 --> 12:41.803
I'm so sorry.

12:41.886 --> 12:43.555
Will you excuse me
for a minute?

12:52.939 --> 12:54.024
No.

12:54.107 --> 12:57.986
No.
You are not pregnant.

13:02.282 --> 13:04.701
Editing my translations,

13:04.784 --> 13:06.745
you always had such confidence

13:06.828 --> 13:08.747
in how they would be received
in English.

13:08.830 --> 13:10.623
You and Camus.

13:10.707 --> 13:13.501
I was still a kid, practically.

13:13.585 --> 13:16.963
Playing masterpiece sandbox,
immersing myself,

13:17.047 --> 13:19.883
working like a dog
with you two nutcases.

13:19.966 --> 13:21.801
I don't know where I found
the confidence.

13:21.885 --> 13:24.262
I remember you were having
an affair

13:24.346 --> 13:27.432
with that fat, boring,
married American.

13:27.515 --> 13:30.935
That fat, boring, married
American is now my husband.

13:31.019 --> 13:32.771
Ah.

13:32.854 --> 13:33.980
Americans.

13:34.064 --> 13:37.108
They can make anything Puritan,
even their affairs.

13:37.192 --> 13:39.652
So devoted
to their mistakes.

13:39.736 --> 13:40.653
You know what?

13:40.737 --> 13:41.696
I think I'm done.

13:46.743 --> 13:48.536
Fancy seeing you here.

13:48.620 --> 13:50.705
Likewise.

13:50.789 --> 13:55.919
Oh, you have a little
hot chocolate mustache.

13:56.002 --> 13:57.462
So do you.

14:00.131 --> 14:02.509
Avis DeVoto,
Jean-Paul Sartre.

14:02.592 --> 14:03.510
Oh.

14:03.593 --> 14:04.969
EnchantÃ©, madame.

14:05.053 --> 14:07.305
Hello.

14:07.389 --> 14:09.724
I actually have to get
back to the hotel.

14:09.808 --> 14:11.059
Oh.

14:11.142 --> 14:12.769
Yeah, I'm desperately behind
with work.

14:12.852 --> 14:16.356
I was hoping our time together
would inspire me

14:16.439 --> 14:18.983
to dive in with newfound vigor.

14:19.067 --> 14:20.694
Oh, well.

14:20.777 --> 14:23.113
I'm waiting
for the next piece, JP.

14:23.196 --> 14:26.116
I do not accept this extension
of your philosophy.

14:27.409 --> 14:29.828
If nothing else, write it down.

14:32.038 --> 14:35.750
Well, uh, it was nice
meeting you.

14:35.834 --> 14:38.503
Oh, don't leave me all alone.

14:38.586 --> 14:40.672
I'll kill myself.

14:40.755 --> 14:43.675
I'm so fucking depressed.

14:43.758 --> 14:46.094
Me too.

14:46.177 --> 14:47.595
He wanted to come in.

14:47.679 --> 14:49.347
Why did you not let him?

14:49.431 --> 14:51.725
To take off your clothes
with another person

14:51.808 --> 14:53.935
is one of life's
only real pleasures,

14:54.019 --> 14:57.981
even if you're as old
and saggy as we are.

14:58.064 --> 15:00.316
It's a butterflies problem.

15:00.400 --> 15:01.818
I don't have them.

15:01.901 --> 15:05.780
With Bernard, my husband,
I always had them.

15:05.864 --> 15:07.657
But he is dead, no?

15:07.741 --> 15:08.700
Yes.

15:08.783 --> 15:10.118
I don't understand.

15:10.201 --> 15:13.204
Stanley is not a replacement
for your husband,

15:13.288 --> 15:14.748
but for loneliness.

15:14.831 --> 15:16.374
Hmm.
Maybe.

15:16.458 --> 15:18.001
It's funny.
You're upset

15:18.084 --> 15:20.337
because Stanley
gives you too much attention.

15:20.420 --> 15:22.213
Try getting too little.

15:22.297 --> 15:24.758
When I come home,
will Simone be there?

15:24.841 --> 15:25.884
I'm guessing no?

15:25.967 --> 15:28.011
I probably won't see her
until morning,

15:28.094 --> 15:29.429
if I'm lucky.

15:29.512 --> 15:32.098
But that's l'amour.

15:32.182 --> 15:34.851
There is always one
who loves the other more.

15:34.934 --> 15:37.437
It's never equal.

15:37.520 --> 15:39.439
My marriage was equal.

15:39.522 --> 15:42.901
I guess you achieved what
Romeo and Juliet could not.

15:42.984 --> 15:44.778
I guess so.

15:44.861 --> 15:48.114
What happened
when your husband took a lover?

15:48.198 --> 15:49.366
He never took a lover.

15:49.449 --> 15:51.785
Well, what about
when you took a lover?

15:51.868 --> 15:53.870
I never took a lover.

15:55.038 --> 15:56.664
C'est impossible.

16:15.433 --> 16:17.268
Aren't they all marvelous,
Julia?

16:17.352 --> 16:18.561
Oh, they are.

16:18.645 --> 16:20.814
Only at Le Cordon Bleu.

16:20.897 --> 16:21.856
Oui.

16:29.447 --> 16:30.448
Oh!

16:50.176 --> 16:51.136
Bon soir.

16:51.219 --> 16:52.178
Bon soir, madame.

16:52.262 --> 16:53.722
I hope you had a pleasant day.

16:53.805 --> 16:55.473
You've obviously never spent
an afternoon

16:55.557 --> 16:57.225
with an existentialist.

16:57.308 --> 16:58.518
Oh.

16:58.601 --> 17:00.603
You have a number of messages.

17:00.687 --> 17:02.105
Oh, look at me.

17:02.188 --> 17:03.982
How popular am I?

17:04.065 --> 17:05.858
They're all coming
from the same person.

17:05.942 --> 17:07.986
Someone named Blanche.

17:08.069 --> 17:09.445
Read them to me.
I can't bear it.

17:09.529 --> 17:11.573
All right.

17:11.656 --> 17:14.742
"I need an update on
the Sylvia Plath estate now!"

17:14.826 --> 17:16.077
There is an exclamation point.

17:17.662 --> 17:18.704
"Where are you?

17:18.788 --> 17:20.790
I thought you were
coming home today."

17:20.874 --> 17:22.416
"I call you at your hotel.

17:22.500 --> 17:24.377
Where are you?"

17:24.461 --> 17:28.089
"People don't answer
their phone in Paris, huh?"

17:28.173 --> 17:30.425
"Your assistant knows nothing."

17:32.761 --> 17:34.262
"I fire your assistant!"

17:34.346 --> 17:36.264
Exclamation point again.

17:36.348 --> 17:37.849
And--

17:41.227 --> 17:44.731
I'll be working in my room
this evening, and ordering in.

17:44.814 --> 17:46.858
- No calls.
- Bien.

17:46.941 --> 17:48.109
Merci.

17:51.613 --> 17:53.031
Staring
at Simone's apartment,

17:53.114 --> 17:56.409
waiting for her or her lover
to emerge post-coital,

17:56.493 --> 18:00.622
doesn't seem to me to be
the best use of time, JP,

18:00.705 --> 18:02.624
even if life is meaningless.

18:02.707 --> 18:05.835
I never said life
is meaningless.

18:05.919 --> 18:08.171
You don't understand
existentialism.

18:08.254 --> 18:09.923
No, I probably don't.

18:10.006 --> 18:11.383
Shoot me.

18:11.466 --> 18:15.178
But didn't you write
"hell is other people"?

18:15.261 --> 18:17.389
Oh, you saw "No Exit"?

18:17.472 --> 18:20.350
No, I read that line
in a magazine.

18:20.433 --> 18:22.936
Then why all these extra people
in your life?

18:23.019 --> 18:25.230
Why this endless parade
of lovers

18:25.313 --> 18:27.440
that drive you crazy
with jealousy?

18:27.524 --> 18:29.859
That seems inconsistent.

18:29.943 --> 18:31.111
You think
I should be consistent?

18:31.194 --> 18:32.904
You are Jean-Paul Sartre.

18:32.987 --> 18:34.656
Is every psychiatrist sane?

18:34.739 --> 18:36.074
Oh, well, you make a point.

18:36.157 --> 18:38.034
Is every priest a saint?

18:38.118 --> 18:39.494
Now you're gloating.

18:39.577 --> 18:41.996
You expect me to live
by my own philosophy

18:42.080 --> 18:43.832
every single second?

18:43.915 --> 18:46.418
This from a woman who believes

18:46.501 --> 18:49.254
that a chance meeting
with a man at the age of 18

18:49.337 --> 18:51.381
was ordained by the universe

18:51.464 --> 18:53.675
as her only shot at happiness?

18:56.928 --> 19:00.974
It made me happy
for a long time.

19:01.057 --> 19:04.686
Isn't that good enough
for a working philosophy?

19:04.769 --> 19:06.354
You should write a book.

19:08.773 --> 19:10.191
So what's the plan?

19:10.275 --> 19:12.444
We wait all night,
if necessary.

19:12.527 --> 19:14.988
- Okay.
- What else?

19:16.364 --> 19:19.200
I know you didn't come
to Paris for me to cook a fish.

19:22.829 --> 19:24.039
No.

19:24.122 --> 19:25.623
It was a very nice fish.

19:28.501 --> 19:31.004
You're looking at me
like it's 1948,

19:31.087 --> 19:34.758
on our first night in France,
and I'm only 36 years old.

19:34.841 --> 19:36.092
No.

19:36.176 --> 19:38.178
I'm looking at you
like it's today,

19:38.261 --> 19:41.264
and I've never changed
how I felt since then.

19:46.895 --> 19:49.064
I've watched
every episode three times,

19:49.147 --> 19:51.149
and I think it's fascinating

19:51.232 --> 19:53.526
how much the show has evolved
in just one season.

19:53.610 --> 19:56.279
And I noticed that things that
were mistakes in episode one,

19:56.363 --> 19:57.864
by episode four,

19:57.947 --> 19:59.949
they were incorporated
into the rhythm of the show.

20:00.033 --> 20:02.869
No, at first Julia's mistakes
gave me angina.

20:02.952 --> 20:05.372
But I figured out
pretty quickly

20:05.455 --> 20:07.999
that the flaws were
the show's greatest strength.

20:08.083 --> 20:09.167
Never cut.

20:09.250 --> 20:10.585
Never start over.

20:10.669 --> 20:13.672
You'll miss something
distinctly Julia.

20:13.755 --> 20:18.093
Over here, it's just
a limitation of our setup.

20:18.176 --> 20:21.221
When you're shooting her moving
from the oven to the counter,

20:21.304 --> 20:23.598
it's very tough to get around
on her on camera three,

20:23.682 --> 20:26.768
so I just come very close
with camera two,

20:26.851 --> 20:29.813
and she knows by now
to cheat to camera.

20:29.896 --> 20:31.981
She's completely instinctive.

20:32.065 --> 20:34.317
Stick close by, Russ.
I'm gonna need you.

20:34.401 --> 20:36.820
As I told Julia,
I'm just down the hall.

20:36.903 --> 20:40.615
May I ask, why did you leave
in the first place?

20:42.075 --> 20:43.535
Because today I got to do
the work

20:43.618 --> 20:46.496
I've been dreaming about
my whole life.

20:46.579 --> 20:52.836
